article.description: Austin Price scored 19 points and made a key 3-pointer to lead Lehigh to a 76-73 victory over Mount St. Mary's on Saturday night.
article.headline: Price makes late 3; Lehigh edges Mount St. Mary's 76-73
article.linkText: Price makes late 3; Lehigh edges Mount St. Mary's 76-73
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- Austin Price scored 19 points and made a key 3-pointer to lead Lehigh to a 76-73 victory over Mount St. Mary's on Saturday night. Charles Glover scored seven points during a 9-2 spurt to give Mount St. Mary's a 73-68 lead with 3:22 to play. John Ross Glover made a 3-pointer, and Price added another 3 from the top of the arc and Lehigh led 74-73 with 47 seconds left. BK Ashe missed a pair of free throws for the Mountaineers, and Kahron Ross made two free throws to stretch the Mountain Hawks' lead to 76-73 with 19 seconds to go. Will Miller tried to draw a foul and attempted an awkward 3-pointer that went under the basket and out of bounds to end it. Kahron Ross added 12 points with nine assists for Lehigh (2-8). Charles Glover scored 22 points to lead Mount St. Mary's (3-8).
